# Goal

Implement a robust, generic, `sessionStorage`-based centralized state manager in `store.js`. Refactor provider pages (`assigned-jobs.js`, `dashboard.js`, `calendar.js`) to read and write synchronously to this centralized state.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]  
> The pages currently use uniquely shaped hardcoded arrays (e.g. `jobs` vs `timelineJobs` vs `events`) which limits data-sharing. To fulfill "changes in Assigned Jobs reflect in Dashboard and Calendar", they all must read from the same `jobs` list!
> 
> **My Approach:**
> In `initData()`, I will load `mockData.json` ONCE. Since you specified not to touch `mockData.json`, I will dynamically map the raw normalized tables (`job_assignments`, `bookings`, `customers`, etc.) within `mockData.json` into a single, unified `jobs` array format that the UI already expects. 
> 
> This unified `jobs` array will be stored in `sessionStorage` and shared across all pages, ensuring changes like "Mark In Progress" correctly appear in the Dashboard and Calendar.

## Proposed Changes

---

### `store.js` Refactor
#### [MODIFY] [store.js](file:///d:/20_TatkuUnited/front-end/js/data/store.js)
Rewrite `store.js` (or add a dedicated centralized API if it strictly adheres to your rules) to export:
1. `initData()` function:
   - Check if `sessionStorage.getItem('fsd_ui_state')` exists.
   - If not, `fetch('mockData.json')`. Build a UI-friendly application state object bridging all the data:
     - `state.jobs` (mapped from `job_assignments` joined with `bookings`).
     - `state.unavailability` (mapped from Provider working hours/blocks).
     - `state.stats` (default stats).
   - `sessionStorage.setItem('fsd_ui_state', JSON.stringify(state))`
2. `getData()` function:
   - `return JSON.parse(sessionStorage.getItem('fsd_ui_state'))`
3. `setData(updatedData)` function:
   - `sessionStorage.setItem('fsd_ui_state', JSON.stringify(updatedData))`

